arXiv:2602.14513v1 Announce Type: new Abstract: In this paper, we construct an explicit rephasing transformation that converts an arbitrary unitary mixing matrix into the Fritzsch--Xing (FX) parametrization, which is obtained by trivializing arguments of the matrix elements in the third row and third column. We further analyzed the rephasing invariant structure of the FX phase $\delta_{m FX}$ under the approximation where the 1-3 element of the diagonalization matrix of charged leptons $U^{e}$ is neglected, $U_{13}^{e} = 0$. As a result, in the limit where the 1-3 element of diagonalization of neutrinos $U^{
u}$ is also neglected, we obtained a compact expression for the FX phase $\delta_{m FX} = \arg [ { U^{e}_{11} U^{e}_{12} U^{e}_{33} } { U^{
u *}_{11} U^{
u *}_{12} U^{
u *}_{33} / \det U^{e} \det U^{
u *} } ] - \arg [ 1 + ({U^{e *}_{23} U^{
u}_{23} / U^{e *}_{33} U^{
u}_{33}} ) ] $. In this limit, the FX phase is controlled by two independent relative phases between $U^{
u, e}$, and the FX phase for finite $U_{13}^{
u}$ is understood as a generalization to the compact expression.
